📖 About
BitHigh is a high school survival game built with Python and Pygame. You pick a character,
manage your stats across 8 months of school life, and try to make it to graduation without
flunking out, burning out, or getting bullied into the ground.

The game runs in two places at once — the Pygame window handles all the visuals and clicking,
while the terminal is where you actually take your quizzes. Keep both open!


🖥️ Requirements
- Python 3.13
- A terminal
- The following Python packages: pygame, ffpyplayer


⚙️ Installation
1. Clone or download the project
git clone https://github.com/yourrepo/bithigh.git
cd bithigh

2. Install dependencies**
pip install pygame ffpyplayer
> ⚠️ ffpyplayer is required for the intro video. The game will crash on startup without it.

3. Run the game — from your terminal
python main.py
> 🖥️ Important: Always launch from the terminal, not by double-clicking the file. The quiz
portions of the game run directly in your terminal window, so you need it open and visible while you play!


🎮 How to Play
Starting Out
1. Launch the game from your terminal (`python main.py`)
2. Watch the intro, then click tart Game
3. Pick your character's gender — your character is chosen randomly from that pool
4. The **NCE Quiz** fires immediately in your terminal. Answer all questions before doing anything else!

The Week Cycle
Each month has 4 weeks, and each week brings a different event:

|        Event         |                    What Happens                     |
|----------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| 👥 Lore Week         | A friend or bully encounter — choose how to respond |
| 🎯 Minigame Week     | A needle-bar minigame in the Pygame window          |
| 📋 Quiz Week         | A subject quiz or long test in your terminal        |
| 🌴 Free Day          | A choice: rest, hang out, study, or read            |

Hit the Skip button in the game window to move to the next week after each event resolves.

The Quizzes (Terminal)
When a quiz triggers, your terminal takes over. The game window will sit still/freeze — that's normal!
- Questions are multiple choice: type `A`, `B`, or `C` and hit Enter
- Questions are grouped by subject and shuffled each time
- Your score is shown at the end before the terminal clears

Pass scores:
|                 Quiz Type                  | Pass Score |
|--------------------------------------------|------------|
| NCE                                        | 8 correct  |
| Subject Quiz (Math, Science, English, Mix) | 6 correct  |
| Long Test / Exam                           | 6 correct  |
| Mix Long Test                              | 8 correct  |
Failing the NCE is an instant game over. Failing subject quizzes and exams just tanks your stats.

The Minigame
A needle bounces left and right across a track. Hit the button when it's inside the green zone.
- 3 rounds per minigame — you need to hit all 3 to pass
- The needle speeds up each round
- The green zone moves to a new position after each hit

Your Stats
Four bars track your school life. Watch them carefully:

| Stat            | High is...                             | Hits zero? |
|-----------------|----------------------------------------|------------|
| 😰 Stress       | Bad — drains happiness over time       |     —      |
| 😊 Happiness    | Good                                   | Game Over  |
| 📝 Grades       | Good                                   | Game Over  |
| 🧠 Intelligence | Good — low grades drain over time      |     —      |
> Stress ≥ 80 drains -5 Happiness every week. Intelligence ≤ 20 drains -5 Grades every week.


💀 Game Overs
There are four ways to lose:
1. Skipping the NCE — you can't opt out
2. Failing the NCE — score below 8
3. Happiness reaches 0 — you break down
4. Grades reach 0 — you get held back


🏆 Winning
Survive all 8 months (32 weeks) and you graduate. Simple. Good luck — you'll need it.


🛠️ Common Issues
Game crashes immediately on startup
Make sure `ffpyplayer` is installed (`pip install ffpyplayer`). It's needed for the intro video.

Quiz doesn't appear / nothing happens after clicking
The quiz runs in your terminal — switch to it! If you launched by double-clicking the script,
the terminal may have closed. Always run with `python main.py` from an open terminal.

`ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'pygame'`
Run `pip install pygame` and try again.

Intro video plays with no sound or skips
This is an ffpyplayer timing thing and doesn't affect gameplay.
